<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76214#p76214"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[So why didn't Nintendo use dual-ported video RAM?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76214#p76214"><![CDATA[
I think the MMC5 has internal dual-ported SRAM for ExRAM.<br /><br />Also I think that even if you have dual ported SRAM, there is issues if you try to acess the same adress from both sides at the same time.<br /><br />The C64 have that "even-odd acess cylces" method to simulate random accessible VRAM, but then the CPU runs at about 0.9 MHz, almost half of the NES, which is really bad.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Apr 05, 2011 3:50 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
