<title type="html"><![CDATA[So why didn't Nintendo use dual-ported video RAM?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76205#p76205"><![CDATA[
Let me hazard a guess: A Z80 would have made it too obvious that Nintendo was <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=5039" class="postlink">homaging the ColecoVision</a> <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /><br /><br />But more likely, a 6502 core takes far less space on the CPU die than a Z80 core, and the space they saved let them put the APU on the same die.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Apr 04, 2011 7:37 pm</p><hr />
