<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76193#p76193"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[So why didn't Nintendo use dual-ported video RAM?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76193#p76193"><![CDATA[
Let's also not forget that we can use DP-SRAM for NES projects today. They would need to be placed on the cart, and the mapper would have to support mapping the secondary port of the VRAM into the CPU address space.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=3706">qbradq</a> — Mon Apr 04, 2011 1:52 pm</p><hr />
