<author><name><![CDATA[psycopathicteen]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-04-04T13:23:24-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-04-04T13:23:24-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76191#p76191</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76191#p76191"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[So why didn't Nintendo use dual-ported video RAM?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7621&amp;p=76191#p76191"><![CDATA[
If VRAM was cheap enough, they could've designed an entire VDP by stringing a bunch of VRAMs together.<br /><br />pixel counter &gt; tile map address<br />tile map data &gt; tile pattern address<br />tile pattern data &gt; color address<br />color data &gt; output<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4383">psycopathicteen</a> — Mon Apr 04, 2011 1:23 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
